270
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:22,060
This is about when I was in 1st Grade of middle school.

271
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:26,430
My math teacher was a man called Mr. Terao.

272
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:30,890
He was such a strange teacher, we nicknamed him "Monsieur Terao".

273
00:13:30,890 --> 00:13:33,960
His hair was naturally curly, but had an undercut and....

274
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:39,820
...he had on coke bottle glasses, while wearing track pants

275
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:45,260
So, anyway, when he's writing on the board, his ass pops out.

276
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,040
'Cuz he writes like this.

277
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:50,200
We can't help chuckling when we see that.

278
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,800
And when we laugh, he goes, *clap, clap*, "You there, no laughing!"

279
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:57,840
He's like, "You there, no laughing".

280
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:01,760
And we'd see that, and laugh again. So that's what he was like.

281
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,910
I liked that teacher, and enjoyed seeing him.

282
00:14:04,910 --> 00:14:09,920
Anyway, around the end of the first semester

283
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:16,590
the teacher came to class with a broken arm, cracked front teeth and scrape marks.

284
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:19,630
And he's casually like, "Okay, let's get started".

285
00:14:19,630 --> 00:14:23,370
But a student asked "Um, err, what happened to you, sir?"

286
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:28,270
and he said, "Well actually, I stayed at school until quite late last night and....

287
00:14:28,280 --> 00:14:31,930
...it was hot so I decided to swim in the pool before going home".

288
00:14:31,930 --> 00:14:36,680
"So, I went to the pool, but the lights were off and it was pitch black".

289
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:39,760
"Anyway, I took off my glasses and jumped in".

290
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:44,320
"I jumped in but, there was no water inside".

291
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,420
What an utter fail!

292
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:52,410
His eyes are so bad he needs coke bottle glasses so...

293
00:14:52,410 --> 00:14:55,710
...he couldn't anything, so when he jumped in he crashed

294
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,760
What a massive fail!

295
00:14:59,210 --> 00:15:01,760
It was an utter fail!

296
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:04,330
He dived straight in?

297
00:15:04,330 --> 00:15:08,030
Everyone who heard that, started laughing....

298
00:15:08,030 --> 00:15:10,940
...and he goes, "No laughing!".

299
00:15:18,010 --> 00:15:21,080
It was the day when they changed the water.

