301
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:25,850
GOTO

302
00:15:25,850 --> 00:15:28,670
Hooooh, I see.

303
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:33,400
In addition to my mother....

304
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:37,400
...my dad is also quite a weird person.

305
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,670
Or rather than weird, should I say, he has no aspirations.

306
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:43,230
He doesn't give kids things to aspire about.

307
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:46,300
I was in the lower grades of primary school and...

308
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:49,610
...on the night of Christmas Eve...

309
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:54,840
...I was waiting impatiently in bed for Santa to bring presents.

310
00:15:54,840 --> 00:16:00,190
I was thinking, "Surely he'll bring presents, even next to my pillow!".

311
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:04,170
So, it was midnight, and I had fallen asleep.

312
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:06,940
The front door slams open and someone yells

313
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:10,220
"HEEEEY!! SANTA'S BACK HOME!"

314
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:13,240
and it was dad returning home.

315
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,590
How obvious.

316
00:16:14,590 --> 00:16:17,310
I was like, "Well this sucks".

317
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:20,540
He screams, "I BOUGHT YA'LL A PRESENT!".

318
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:23,640
He even gives away that he bought it.

319
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,230
He's saying everything.

320
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:29,370
And he goes "Oh, sleepin' soundly eh? I'll leave your present here!".

321
00:16:29,370 --> 00:16:31,900
I pretended to be asleep...

322
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:35,500
...thinking, "Oh well, he got me a present, it's okay I guess."

323
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:39,850
The next morning I woke up excited to open it up

324
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:43,820
so I looked next to my pillow, and the present was a library book.

325
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:50,780
A library book!

326
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,780
He borrowed it!

327
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:55,680
Yes, and I had to go return it 2 days later!

328
00:16:58,570 --> 00:17:03,640
And the book was also called, "New Years Around The World".

329
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,640
It has nothing to do with Christmas!

330
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:08,920
He's already thinking of something 1 week later!

331
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:13,390
It's hard to tell if he has aspirations or not.

332
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:17,980
It's starting to be a bit one-sided today.

