TSUKAJI

375
00:20:05,870 --> 00:20:07,580
Maybe it's Tsukaji day today?

376
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:12,920
Well, let's see...this is a story of when I was in middle school.

377
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,880
At the time, Bebop Highschool was very popular and...

378
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:19,720
...it was a time when everyone looked up to delinquents.

379
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:24,600
There were incidences like people getting hunted for uniforms by kids from other schools.

380
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:28,780
Anyway, when I was in 3rd grade of middle school

381
00:20:28,780 --> 00:20:32,140
there was like an uprising of the 2nd years.

382
00:20:32,250 --> 00:20:34,250
Yes, there was a strange time like that.

383
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:39,020
Anyway, one day after school, I think in summer...

384
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:41,550
I was changing in the kendo club locker room when...

385
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:46,840
five of the 3rd year delinquent guys came in.

386
00:20:46,840 --> 00:20:51,050
But they were all friends of mine from primary school...

387
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:55,710
and they said "We're going to go and brawl with the 2nd graders now".

388
00:20:55,710 --> 00:21:00,170
This was because the 2nd graders wouldn't pay respect to the 3rd graders.

389
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:02,990
As they thought they were tougher than 3rd years.

390
00:21:02,990 --> 00:21:07,820
They wanted all 3rd graders to greet 2nd graders, or something.

391
00:21:07,820 --> 00:21:12,160
They wanted to gather as many fighters as they could, so they asked me to come.

392
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:15,930
I wasn't necessarily a fierce guy, but they were all my friends so....

393
00:21:15,930 --> 00:21:18,720
I said "Ok, I'll go", and so I did.

394
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:24,200
And seriously, there was about thirty 3rd graders gathered near a lake

395
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,200
waiting for the 2nd graders.

396
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:29,040
Eventually the 2nd graders appeared and...

397
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:35,050
there were only about 20, but they all had wooden swords and kendo sticks.

398
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:39,070
The 3rd graders were yelling like, "Hey, those cheaters have wooden swords and stuff!".

399
00:21:39,070 --> 00:21:42,440
When I looked closer, they were all from my club.

400
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:46,920
They were the wooden swords and bamboo sticks from my kendo clubroom

401
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:50,200
and since I was kendo captain I was worried about getting in trouble

402
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,750
and peoples' kendo stick getting wrecked.

403
00:21:52,990 --> 00:21:57,130
When I looked at their leader, the stick that he held

404
00:21:57,130 --> 00:22:01,800
was the stick that I use for official bouts, and take extremely good care of!

405
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:04,330
I used to repair the leather on it...

406
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:09,900
...and even the tsuba, I went all the way from Osaka to a shop in Wakayama to get it!

407
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:09,900
The tsuba is the hand guard on the sword.

408
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:13,870
I knew for sure it was mine!

409
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:16,840
Anyway, a junior from the kendo club looking sorry over there.

410
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:20,080
He was my junior, so I was like "What the heck are ya doin'!?"

411
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:24,650
"I've got a fight in one month, and I was planning to use that stick so....

412
00:22:24,650 --> 00:22:26,970
...I'm gonna be pissed if it breaks!"

413
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:29,630
But then everyone was going "Let's gooooo!".

414
00:22:29,630 --> 00:22:33,640
and the 3rd and 2nd graders were all out brawling

415
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:37,660
while I found that junior, and was yelling "Why did ya give it to him!?"

416
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:39,450
"Why did ya give everyone kendo sticks!!"

417
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:42,680
While everyone was arguing about who's gonna greet who,

418
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:46,380
I just kept banging on about the kendo sticks.

419
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:49,210
Well, that's quite an incident.

