00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,120
MATSUMOTO

421
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:54,590
So now's, the time?

422
00:22:54,590 --> 00:23:02,600
Well I think you've begun to sense that my mum is also quite strange.

423
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:05,080
This happened today. Seriously, today.

424
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:09,100
A certain tv program showed me doing the opening baseball pitch at a game

425
00:23:09,100 --> 00:23:12,800
and my mum called me saying, "That was nice....." and stuff.

426
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:15,850
She often lies a lot. She said, "It was nice....

427
00:23:15,850 --> 00:23:18,780
EVERYONE in Amagasaki is saying so."

428
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:18,830
Amagasaki: Matsumoto's home town.

429
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:22,840
As if they would be.

430
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,570
That's definitely a lie!

431
00:23:26,570 --> 00:23:32,170
She's a strange mother, but when I was about 20 years old...

432
00:23:32,170 --> 00:23:34,920
Well, actually, I'm the youngest out of three children and...

433
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:39,290
...I had turned 20, so she said that she was lonely.

434
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:45,150
And she said "You've all become adults, so I want another child."

435
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:48,330
But it's kinda impossible for her to bear a child at her age.

436
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:51,770
Anyway, I don't know what she was thinking but

437
00:23:51,770 --> 00:23:56,110
when I came home one day, she was holding a toy baby...

438
00:23:56,110 --> 00:24:00,520
...and said, "From today, this is my child".

439
00:24:01,630 --> 00:24:04,200
She even named it Akira!

440
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:08,910
She's like "Ain't that right, Akira? Ain't that riiight?"

441
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:12,750
That's creepy!

442
00:24:12,750 --> 00:24:17,630
And when I come home at night she'd wander out while holding Akira.

443
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:23,640
She's say "Just heat up that curry for dinner! Heat up the curry!"

444
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:27,040
"Ain't that right, Akira? Ain't that riiight?"

445
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:27,880
Scary, right?

446
00:24:28,030 --> 00:24:29,000
Yeahhh.

447
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:33,180
But 2 months later, Akira was abandoned and lying like this.

448
00:24:37,610 --> 00:24:42,440
She's a really creepy mother.

449
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,720
Here we go then.

450
00:24:44,830 --> 00:24:46,890
CHIHARA

451
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,890
Ummm....

452
00:24:48,890 --> 00:24:51,610
This just happened the other day.

453
00:24:51,610 --> 00:24:57,130
Currently, the Yoshimoto Shinkigeki is visiting all around the country for their national tour.

454
00:24:57,130 --> 00:25:01,930
So people like Imada, Itao, Kimu-nii and others do various stuff

455
00:25:01,930 --> 00:25:07,470
but the practice for that occurs in the Lumine at midnight after all other shows end.

456
00:25:07,470 --> 00:25:10,800
Anyway, I love Shishaku Shisho and always listen

457
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:13,930
to his rakugo tapes while driving to practice.

458
00:25:13,930 --> 00:25:17,480
Lumine has an underground car park so I parked there and went up in the elevator

459
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,160
to practice with them at night.

460
00:25:19,160 --> 00:25:23,660
Then my manager says "Excuse me, can I please borrow your car keys?"

461
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:25,230
so I asked why,

462
00:25:25,230 --> 00:25:30,990
and he said that there was nighttime construction going on, and the cars had to be moved outside for a bit.

463
00:25:30,990 --> 00:25:34,480
So they had to take out everyone's cars, including Imada and Kimu-Nii.

464
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:37,850
I was like, "Okay, go ahead then".

465
00:25:37,850 --> 00:25:42,080
but my managaer, Inagaki, is a paper driver, and has never driven once since getting his license.

466
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:48,590
So, I assumed he'd pass the key to one of the many other Yoshimoto managers and get them to move my car.

467
00:25:48,590 --> 00:25:51,710
So he went off to do that, and practice finished around 3:30am.

468
00:25:51,710 --> 00:25:56,010
We began to leave, and they announced that Imada's car had been returned to the car park.

469
00:25:56,010 --> 00:26:01,050
So Imada leaved, and then next Kimu-nii's car came, so he leaved.

470
00:26:01,050 --> 00:26:05,960
But mine wouldn't come at all! Even after waiting 30 minutes!

471
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:10,250
It was strange so I went downstairs, but it wouldn't come

472
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:15,360
so I walked to the car park where they said they moved it to

473
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:19,050
when some other guy's manager came and said

474
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:23,080
"I'm sorry, Inagaki crashed your car".

475
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:27,150
"Whaaat!? Why did you let Inagaki drive it?!"

476
00:26:27,150 --> 00:26:30,670
But you know how Yoshimoto is like.

477
00:26:30,670 --> 00:26:32,720
Inagaki probably said he can't drive

478
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:36,860
but his seniors were probably like "I don't give a damn! We're low on help!!"

479
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:40,300
So he probably was forced to drive for the first time since being licensed.

480
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:43,980
When I went to the car park, the head lights were off

481
00:26:43,980 --> 00:26:48,280
and it was slightly ahead of the park space, and the doors were wide open.

482
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:52,240
I look at the front and there's a massive dent.

483
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:53,930
Quite a huge dent.

484
00:26:53,930 --> 00:26:58,540
I was like, "How did you hit it there!?", it was right down the middle!

485
00:26:58,540 --> 00:26:59,540
Yeah just from parking?

486
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:02,920
I looked up and Inagaki was there with a horribly sorry face

487
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:05,500
saying, "I'm so sorry! I'm so sorry!"

488
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:09,480
but from the car I can hear Shishaku Shishou's comedy routine.

489
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:14,570
Also, he was telling a story was about winning the lottery

490
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:19,150
and was yelling "I hit it! I hit it! I hit the jackpot!"

491
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:26,060
I'd never seen people laughing at Shishaku Shishou as much as that time.

492
00:27:30,810 --> 00:27:32,810
Wowww.

493
00:27:32,810 --> 00:27:35,680
Woow, that's amazing.

494
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:36,960
Maan.

495
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:39,950
Sure is funny.

